    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in **Corbin Carroll** (85.94), who remains the cornerstone of our SB-scarcest strategy. **Corbin Carroll** is our strongest play, bolstered by a plus-matchup against Sean Burke and, crucially, a slow pitcher delivery profile that projects a 100% stolen base success probability. He is flanked by high-efficiency upside in **James Wood** (76.28) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.98), both of whom exploit favorable park factors and the exploitable 6.36 and 5.43 xERAs of their respective opponents. **Brice Turang** (74.51) and **Trevor Story** (74.11) round out the top tier, with **Trevor Story** specifically benefiting from a massive 19% SP skill boost against a shaky Gil, providing the power-speed balance necessary to climb the roto standings.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Giancarlo Stanton** (48.48), who hovered near the 50-point threshold but ultimately lacked the categorical efficiency required to displace our current starters. Despite a decent park factor, he struggles against the southpaw Early, and the optimizer prioritized the positional versatility and higher scoring floors of **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Josh Naylor**. We are closely monitoring a 42% rain risk for **Dalton Rushing**, whose 51.31 score is already dampened by a projected #9 spot in the order; should the game be delayed, we are prepared to pivot to more reliable production. While **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (47.11) and **Max Muncy** (47.58) provide depth, their poor platoon matchups today keep them firmly on the pine as we prioritize maximizing our daily efficiency scores.",
